T1	Participants 1900 2071	CONCLUSIONS As a high proportion of patients treated with tamoxifen eventually required surgery treatment of elderly patients with breast cancer should include mastectomy.
T2	Participants 1365 1484	MAIN RESULTS Mortality from metastatic cancer in tamoxifen group was 7 (10.6%) and in mastectomy group 10 (15.3%) (NS).
T3	Participants 100 205	STUDY OBJECTIVE Comparison of tamoxifen and mastectomy in treatment of breast cancer in elderly patients.
T4	Participants 0 98	Comparison of mastectomy with tamoxifen for treating elderly patients with operable breast cancer.
T5	Participants 441 628	PATIENTS 135 consecutive patients with breast cancer aged over 70 with operable tumours (less than 5 cm maximum diameter); 68 were allocated to tamoxifen group and 67 to mastectomy group.
